bronze /brɒnz/

1. N-UNCOUNT Bronze is a yellowish-brown metal which is a mixture of copper and tin. 青铜 

例： ...a bronze statue of Giorgi Dimitrov. …一座乔治·季米特洛夫铜像。 

2. COLOR Something that is bronze is yellowish-brown in colour. 青铜色的 

例： Her hair shone bronze and gold. 她的头发闪耀着青铜色和金黄色的光彩。

